tags: what do you think of the title sequence?
summary:
Have a look at the the title sequence! :)

  Update - transcription of the letter for accessibility: Dear Everybody, I know that...
caption:
Have a look at the the title sequence! :)

Update - transcription of the letter for accessibility:

Dear Everybody,

I know that people are getting slightly desperate to know when GOOD OMENS is being released. Apparently, “Spring 2019” just isn’t enough.

So here you go.

Here’s the lavish launch date. And more than that - here’s Peter Anderson studio’s glorious title sequence - glorious animation, and David Arnold’s magnificent music to go with it. 

And as a bonus, a new piece of Art for you.

I hope it leaves you, like Crowley and Aziraphale, on top of the world.

Sorry about the World Ending,

Neil Gaiman.

– Whatever the hell catches my fancy
– Fandom love! This includes CURRENTLY ABOUT 300% GOOD OMENS, Pacific Rim, Sherlock Holmes in any shape and form, Lotr/the Hobbit, my newly re-awakened love for Doctor Who, Star Trek TOS,
